      "role": "user",
      "content": "got it. so it has to be deep enough to be in that tension zone. but once it's all poured and hardened, it's like this whole hidden network of steel inside a solid block that you can't see anymore. is there any way engineers can actually tell if the rebar was placed correctly or if something went wrong deep inside the structure once it's set?",
