      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, engineers have several methods to inspect rebar placement, such as ground-penetrating radar (GPR) which sends pulses to detect the steel's location, or coring to physically inspect the concrete's interior. However, it is important to note that while these tests can reveal issues, they are often destructive or costly, so prevention through strict quality control during the pour is usually the best strategy. If you are worried about hidden defects, you might consider asking your professor if they have any case studies on structural monitoring using these technologies.",
